# PSBT Analyzer — REST / HTTP client requests
#
# For VS Code: install the "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client), open
# this file, set @baseUrl if needed, and click "Send Request" above a block.
# IntelliJ / WebStorm: built-in HTTP Client supports the same format.
#
# Start the app first:  uvicorn psbt_tool.api.main:app --reload
#
# @psbtB64 — minimal segwit test PSBT (same as tests.fixtures.segwit_two_output_psbt).
# For the upload request, generate a file first, e.g.:
#   python scripts/generate_psbt.py -i 2 -o 2 -f 10 --per-output 100000
#   then fix the path in the upload block to match the generated .psbt name.

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000
@psbtB64 = 

### App health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Mempool: recommended fee rates (same source as the analyzer UI)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/fees/recommended

### Analyze PSBT (JSON, base64)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/psbt/analyze
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "psbt_base64": "{{psbtB64}}"
}

### Analyze PSBT (form: single field `psbt` — base64 or hex)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/psbt/analyze/text
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

psbt={{psbtB64}}

### Analyze PSBT (file upload) — path is relative to this file in scripts/
# Adjust filename if your generated file differs; create with generate_psbt.py
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/psbt/analyze/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----psbtBnd

------psbtBnd
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="local.psbt"
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

< ../generated_psbts/demo.psbt
------psbtBnd--

### Coin-sim: build a pre-filled sim request from a PSBT
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/coin-sim/bootstrap
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "psbt_base64": "{{psbtB64}}"
}

### Coin-sim: run selection strategies
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/coin-sim/run
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "utxos": [
    {
      "outpoint": "aabbccdd00000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000000:0",
      "value_sats": 200000,
      "script_type": "P2WPKH"
    }
  ],
  "targets": [
    {
      "address": "bc1qar0srrr7xfkvy5l643lydnw9re59gtzzwf5mdq",
      "script_type": "P2WPKH",
      "value_sats": 100000
    }
  ],
  "change_script_type": "P2WPKH",
  "fee_rate_sat_vb": 2.0,
  "dust_threshold_sats": 546,
  "strategies": ["largest_first", "smallest_first", "branch_and_bound"]
}

### Apply structured edits (no-op: empty `ops` list; add EditOp objects to mutate)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/psbt/apply
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "psbt_base64": "{{psbtB64}}",
  "ops": []
}
